President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring June 14, 2013, as Flag Day and the week beginning June 9, 2013, as National Flag Week. The proclamation calls for the display of the American flag on all Federal Government buildings during that week and urges all Americans to observe Flag Day and National Flag Week by displaying the flag. The proclamation also encourages the people of the United States to honor America and celebrate their heritage through public gatherings and activities, as well as publicly recite the Pledge of Allegiance to the Flag of the United States of America.